  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Contract Manager (Tender focus)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist in the preparation and compilation of tender submissions including technical proposals, pricing, and contractual terms.</li>\n  <li>Analyse tender documents (e.g. drawings, specifications, conditions of contract) and identify risks, clarifications, and requirements.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with internal departments (QS, engineering, procurement) and external stakeholders (consultants, suppliers, subcontractors) to gather tender inputs.</li>\n  <li>Ensure accurate and timely submission of tenders in accordance with client requirements.</li>\n  <li>Maintain and update the tender tracking system, and support pre- and post-tender clarifications.</li>\n  <li>Assist in cost estimation, BOQ review, and value engineering proposals.</li>\n  <li>Support the Contract Manager in negotiating terms and conditions for awarded contracts.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with legal and regulatory requirements in tender and contract processes.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Requirements:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Quantity Surveying, Building, Construction Management, Engineering, or related discipline.</li>\n  <li>5-8 years of experience in tendering or contracts administration in the construction/engineering sector.</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of contract types and tender processes.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in MS Office and contract management software.</li>\n  <li>Strong analytical, organizational, and communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Able to work under pressure and meet strict deadlines.</li>\n  <li>Experience in school and hotel project tenders.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with local tender platforms and procurement systems.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of legal and financial aspects of contracting.</li>\n</ul>",
